results.details: MoPub is a one-stop ad serving platform designed to help mobile app publishers optimize their ad inventory on iOS and Android devices.  We work with mobile application publishers to turn their apps into businesses. Unlike other ad servers, exchanges, and mediation networks that only provide one solution, MoPub manages all your advertising inventory needs – including direct ads, house ads, ad network mediation, and real-time bidding campaigns through MoPub Marketplace – all in one product.  MoPub's single, open-source and flexible SDK means you get complete control over and transparency into your revenue sources. Prioritize specific campaigns and track your results – all through a completely intuitive UI.  Email info@mopub.com to find out more!

results.details:
2014 Cartoon Art Museum Fundraiser: #NeXTEVNT

Looking Back at NeXTSTEP, meeting old friends and making new ones

The Cartoon Art Museum (CAM), the only institution in the western United States dedicated to all forms of cartoons and comics, presents the third annual #NeXTEVNT fundraiser on Monday, June 2, 2014. 

Hosted by longtime Objective-C hacker, Pixarian, and CAM board member (in order of seniority: 25 yrs, 21 yrs, 12 yrs) Dr. Michael B. Johnson, this lively evening will feature a number of special guests from back in the day, including former solidThinking developer and current VP of Tools at Pixar Guido Quaroni, ur-NeXTSTEP developer Andy Stone, and several others too shy to let us give out their names (some of whom might work at a local fruit company).

There will be a bunch of NeXTStations running NeXTSTEP 3.3 or OpenStep 4.2 (including a rare HP workstation) along with lots of third-party software from back in the day as well as the folks who wrote it. We've also heard rumors that there may be a VMware version of NeXTSTEP 3.3 and OpenStep 4.2, but we can neither confirm nor deny.

Other highlights include:

musical entertainment courtesy of our friend James Dempsey.
rarely seen photos from photographer Doug Menuez. Steve Jobs commissioned to shoot all internal NeXT events back at the beginning - http://www.menuez.com
Chris Coleman from 20 Wines will be pouring awesome California vintages (in his signature ammo cases, of course).
a local SF food truck, hearty beer from Thirsty Bear, some choice tequila and whiskey options, and a variety of non-alchoholic drinks.
the museum's current exhibitions, including Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and Pretty in Ink: The Trina Robbins Collection.
There are even rumors of a raffle/auction with some interesting NeXT & Pixar items, but this is entirely unconfirmed at this time. If there was such a thing, it would only be available to ticket holders...

Tickets & Event Info

Tickets are priced at $200 each, and include entry to the event, plus a personalized NeXTEVNT ID badge. The ID badge can help identify you amongst other NeXTEVNT guests, and will include your Twitter username (or first name if you prefer), company name, and a small sentence describing a funny story about your experience with NeXT or fun fact.

This event starts at 4 p.m. to allow you plenty of time to enjoy the museum and chill before eating, drinking, and listening to our speakers. We want this event to be about hanging out and chatting, which is what we heard that folks most enjoyed last year.

Event Sponsorship

We’re looking for sponsors to help fund this event. The sponsorship will pay for the food & drink for the event, plus help sponsor some educational programs for kids. In return we’re offering 3 levels of sponsorship:

Platinum – $2,000 (4 tickets & company logo printed on the ID badge (Front Side))
Gold – $1,000 (2 tickets & large company logo printed on the ID badge (Back Side))
Silver – $500 (1 ticket & small company logo printed on the ID badge (Back Side))
Tax Deductions

Please note that most of the ticket price for this event is tax deductible. You will receive an email from the museum with details you can use use for tax purposes. The museum is a 501c3 non-profit organization. For a list of Bay Area companies that match employee contributions, click here.

About the Cartoon Art Museum

Founded in 1984, the Cartoon Art Museum is the only museum in the western United States dedicated to cartoons and comics.  The museum was started by a group of cartoonists and collectors who wanted to share their appreciation of this unique art form with the rest of the world.  The museum is dedicated to the collection, preservation, study and exhibition of original cartoon art in all forms to benefit historians, cartoonists, journalists, artists, collectors and the general public.
results.title: Fundraiser: #NeXTEVNT

results.details:
WHAT
The Aero Adventure is a Bluetooth Low Energy beacon scavenger
hunt across a designated area around San Francisco near WWDC 2014 
that will engage players utilizing iBeacon™ 
and CoreBluetooth in order to solve a puzzle for prizes.
Tell me more

WHERE
The AERO Adventure will take place in a designated area within South of Market and Union Square.

Adventure beacons can be found easily using basic BLE apps and will be within the designated boundaries.

All but one beacon will be located outside in public spaces.

Click the map on the left for boundary lines.

WHEN
The AERO Adventure will run for 72 hours the week of WWDC 2014 beginning Sunday 8PM PDT and end Wednesday 8PM PDT.

An exclusive Clue Card will be handed out Sunday evening between 8PM & 9PM. Email adventure (at) discoveraero.com with subject 'Clue' to find out where you can get yours.

Winners will be drawn and announced on this site and social media by 9PM Wednesday evening.

WHY
The AERO Adventure gives conference goers the opportunity to dabble with iBeacon, CoreBluetooth and micro-location with the intent of giving everyone a little exercise and taking in just a small part of what San Francisco offers.

Or if you prefer... because it's fun! Duh.
RULES
No cost to participate
No registration required
One submission per person*
Submit solution to adventure ( at ) discoveraero.com
Attendance not required at either venue to participate or win
Please be respectful of other people and property
No moving, possessing or tampering physically or digitally of AERO Adventure beacons
Please have fun and be safe!
 
* The answer will be obvious so no need to guess
ET CETERA
Submisions
A minimum submission should include the subject 'Solved' with the body containing the solution to the puzzle. Please include a valid email if different than what you are sending with. Any additional information is optional but helpful in establishing contact in the event of winning a prize. We will not sell, rent, or otherwise share personal information without consent.
 
Prizes
Submissions with the correct solution will be drawn randomly except for the First Solved Prize which will be awarded to the first person to correctly solve the puzzle. The First Solved winner will still be placed in the random drawing.
First Solved: $50
First Place: $100
Second Place: $70
Third Place: $30
 
Clue
Each AERO Adventure beacon will display a different number when scanned. This will be important in solving the puzzle.
 
Apps
The AERO Adventure beacons will make use of two services within iOS for Bluetooth Low Energy;
First, iBeacon is used for anyone wishing to utilize an iBeacon app for receiving notifications when in range of a beacon during the hunt. The Proximity UUID for all beacons will be E2C56DB5-DFFB-48D2-B060-D0F5A71096E0 which is an iOS test ID that should be recognized by most current iBeacon apps. The Major ID will be 108 and the Minor ID will be the number of the beacon as per its Display Name.
Second, you can manually scan for beacons along the way using CoreBluetooth scanners such as BLExplr, LightBlue and others. Search for BLE or BTLE in the app store.
 
WWDC
The AERO Adventure is not affiliated with nor endorsed by Apple or WWDC. It is our sincere intention to enhance NOT to disrupt WWDC in any way. No AERO Adventure beacons will be in or on the Moscone West campus. As such it is expected that all adventurers will refrain from searching, scanning or otherwise playing the game while attending the conference. However, what you do outside of the Moscone West conference walls on your own time is your choice.
Many Happy Adventures!
~ The AERO Team
results.title: Aero Adventure WWDC 2014

Grab a bite, grab a seat, and sit back and watch as Apple unveils their recent developments. Feel free to engage in play-by-play commentary with your fellow developers. 

About Çingleton: 
The Çingleton Symposium is a focal point for developers, designers and others to gather for a weekend of thought provoking talks, discussions and networking in beautiful Old Montreal, Canada. This year it will be taking place October 10-12, 2014.

results.details:
In 2009, when Twitter was first starting to take off, a rich constellation of Twitter clients appeared. One of the brightest stars of that time was Birdfeed, one of the few great Twitter readers for iPhone at a time when Twitter had no iOS app of its own (it later acquired Tweetie, which became Twitter for iPhone). Birdfeed was popular among the tech-focused early adopters of Twitter and was acquired by Brizzly in 2010.
In this talk, Buzz will explain how Birdfeed came about, what made it special, and what he learned from building iOS apps in an API ecosystem. He'll also dish a little dirt on the contentious third party Twitter app scene.
 
Event Details
6:30-7:00 Food and drink
7:00-8:30 Talk and Q&A with Buzz Andersen
8:30-9:00 Networking
results.title: [Hack, Deploy, Scale] Hearts of Darkness

Are you an iOS developer or startup person looking for that one beautifully designed app to get involved with at an early stage? 
Then this event is just for you. 
Meet the teams behind some of San Francisco's hottest design-led apps in the making. Having made a splash at this year's festivals including Launch and NYC Disrupt, they'll be introducing themselves and demoing their startups. 
The event location is hosted by the design consultancy, Neo and sponsored by mobile technology firm, Thomson Reuters. Guests will be provided with drinks and refreshments.

Paperfold - Launch 2014 
www.paperfold.me 
Paperfold has found a way to make email look and feel beautiful and become more productive. Recently visiting  from London to San Francisco, they aim to radically redesign your inbox with content just one tap away.
 
Fetch - NYC Disrupt 2014 
www.buywithfetch.com
Fetch has found an easy way to buy things through your smartphone, at the best price and from just a photo or a text message. Powered by real people, they'll place the order and shipping information in just one tap.
